
<!-- Inladen van de header (navbar) via Liquid partials -->
{% render 'partials/header.liquid' %}
<!-- Inladen van de css -->

{% render 'partials/head.liquid' %}

   <!-- Navigatie met een terug-knop voor gebruiksvriendelijkheid -->
   <section class="detail-artwork">
    <div class="container">
      <nav>
        <a href="/" title="Terug naar de homepagina">
        <button type="button" class="back-button">
          ← BACK
        </button>
      </a>
      </nav>
  
    <!-- Sectie met het artwork en de afbeelding -->
    <article class="object-detail">
      <img
        class="artwork-image"
        src="https://fdnd-agency.directus.app/assets/{{ artwork.image }}"
        alt="Afbeelding van het artwork: {{ artwork.title }}">
      <div class="artwork-title">{{ artwork.title }}</div>
    </article>


    <div class="info-container">
      <!-- Hoofdsectie met informatie over het artwork -->
      <section class="info-left">
        <header>
          <h1>Portraits Sketched from the Life Since the Year 1793</h1>

          <!-- Informatie over het museum -->
          <div class="museum-header">
            <img
              src="/assets/museum-icon.png"
              alt="Logo van Museum "
              width="40"
              height="40">
            <p>
              <strong>Museum of Lorem Ipsum</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </header>

        <!-- Beschrijving van het artwork -->
        <p>
          Bowl with monochrome luster decoration. The design shows an antelope confronting a long-tailed bird on a background of small chevrons. The kufic inscription on the body of the antelope says: “blessing to its owner.“ Above the antelope, the artist inscribed his name: “work of ‘Ali.“ In the middle of the glazed foot, the word Baraka (blessing) is rendered in kufic script. The initially abstract design style of the Abbasid luster wares developed in the 10th century and particularly in Iraq into a new decorative approach with animal designs. These are usually set on a stippled background. By this time, potters had abandoned polychrome painting in favor of monochrome luster. Here, a single animal or a symmetrical pair was at the center of the design. The change of style may reflect the taste of the new elite formed when the Buyids arrived in Iraq.

      </section>

      <!-- Extra details over het artwork -->
      <aside class="info-right">
        <section class="artwork-details">
          <p>
            <strong>Titel:</strong>
            {{ artwork.title }}</p>
          {% if artwork.slug %}
            <p>
              <strong>Slug:</strong>
              {{ artwork.slug }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </section>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- het laatste gedeelte met de 4 images  -->
<section class="related-artworks">
  <h2>You may also like</h2>
  <div class="related-container">
    {% for related in relatedArtworks %}
      <div class="related-item">
        <img src="https://fdnd-agency.directus.app/assets/{{ related.image }}" alt="Afbeelding van {{ related.title }}">
        <p>
          <strong>{{ related.title }}</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <div class="surprise-button">
    <button type="button">→ SURPRISE ME</button>
  </div>
</section>